<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-13T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-13T02:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890G.002/149: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister Resident in Iraq</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Knabenshue</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Baghdad</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-13T10:00:00+03:00">April 13, 1941—10
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 11:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>79. Foreign Office telegraphed [<hi rend="italic">telephoned?</hi>]
                                today saying Minister for Foreign Affairs would receive visits of
                                congratulations from chiefs of diplomatic missions tomorrow morning.
                                British, Turkish, Egyptian, Iranian, French and American will not
                                attend leaving only the Japanese and Italian.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Knabenshue</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>